Description: Limestone model of a vase: with a handle running from the rim to the shoulder. The handle has not been undercut, but is represented as a solid ridge. Hollowing restricted to a slight depression in the top. The exterior is decorated with a network of lines in black paint.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tomb of Qaa, tomb Q.20 subsidiary burial
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, 15, 28, pl.XXXVIII, 5-6.
